                         subTitle: '',
                         content: `<br/><em><span style="font-weight:900;color:#FF000A;font-size:larger"> Narada said:  </span>
                         <ol><li> 0 Brahma, the sinless and the intelligent one, you have splendidly narrated the story of Siva and Siva. My life has been sanctified. This is conducive to my benefit.</li>
                         <li>Now please tell me, what the boon was that Daksha with steady sacred rites and austere penance, secured from the Goddess, and how she became Daksha's daughter</li>
                            <br/><em><span style="font-weight:900;color:white;text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px grey;background-color:silver;font-size:x-large"font-size:larger">Shree Brahma said:  </span>

                         <li>0 Narada, listen. You are blessed. You are revered by all sages with devotion. Hear how with good sacred rites, performed penance and secured boons.</li>
                         <li>At my bidding, the intelligent Daksha, the great chief controlled his mind and went to worship the Goddess, the mother of the universe, with that cherished desire.</li>
                         <li>He went to the northern shore of the ocean of milk  and began to perform the penance, keeping the mother of the universe in his heart. He wished to see the
                         Goddess in person. </li>
                         <li>For three thousand divine years he performed the penance with good sacred rites, controlling his mind and keeping himself pure.</li>
                         <li>For some years, he sustained himself on taking in only air, abstaining from food, for some years taking only water and for some years taking only leaves as food. Thus he
                         spent the time meditating upon the Goddess in cosmic form.</li>
                         <li>He was intensively devoted to the meditation of the Goddess. He was engaged in the penance for a long time. With sacred rites and various restraints he worshipped the .
                         Goddess.</li>
                         <li>0 excellent sage, then Siva appeared in person to who maintained all restraints, Yama<noteref1_note1footer>(1) - (253)</note> etc. and worshipped the mother of the universe.</li>
                         <li>On seeing the mother of the universe cosmic in form, the lord of the subjects considered himself well rewarded.</li>
                         <li>With various sorts of prayer he eulogised and bowed to the Goddess mother of the universe, Kalika seated on a lion, dark-complexioned, with four arms and
                         beautiful face, the bestower of the boon, the abode of safety, holding a blue lotus and the sword in her hands, comely
                         with reddish eyes and with beautiful dishevelled hair. </li>
                         <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:maroon;font-size:larger"> Daksa said:  </span>
                         <li>Obeisance to Thee, 0 great Goddess, mother of the universe, wielding the great illusion, the ruler of the universe. It is with great favour that Thou showed Thy own body to
                         me.</li>
                         <li>Be pleased, 0 primordial Goddess, be pleased, 0 
                         Goddess in the form of Siva; be pleased, 0 bestower of boons to the devotees; obeisance be to Thee, 0 wielder of illusion
                         over the universe.  </li>
                         <br/><em><span style="font-weight:900;color:white;text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px grey;background-color:silver;font-size:x-large"font-size:larger">Shree Brahma said:  </span>
                        <li>0 sage, thus eulogised by Daskha of purified soul, the Goddess spoke to him although she knew what his desire was </li>
                        <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:#ff4811;ffont-size:x-large"font-size:larger"> The Goddess Said  </span>
                        <li>0 Daksha I am very much delighted by your great devotion. Choose a boon according to your desire. There is nothing which shall not be granted to you. </li>
                        <br/><em><span style="font-weight:900;color:white;text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px grey;background-color:silver;font-size:x-large"font-size:larger">Shree Brahma said:  </span>
                        <li>On hearing the words of the mother of the universe, Daksa Prajapati was very happy and he said to Siva
                        after bowing to her frequently. </li>    
                        <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:maroon;font-size:larger"> Daksa said:  </span>
                        <li>0 wielder of great illusion, 0 mother of the universe, if you wish to grant me any boon please listen to my words with pleasure. Be pleased to fulfil my desire.</li>
                        <li>My lord and master Siva has manifested Himself as Brahma's son in the name of Rudra. He is the perfect and full:fledged incarnation of the supreme soul.</li>
                        <li>You have not so far incarnated. Who will be His wife ? Hence 0 Siva, take an incarnation on the Earth and fascinate the great lord.</li>
                        <li>Excepting you, no other lady will ever be competent to enthral Hence be born as my daughter and become Siva's consort.</li>
                        <li>Exhibiting your divine sports as this, 0 Goddess, you be the enchantress of Siva, this is the only boon I crave of you. I speak out the truth to you.</li>
                        <li>This fulfils my own interests. Indeed it fulfils the interests of all the worlds as well as those of Brahma, and Siva. Hence I have been induced by Brahma in this 
                        direction</li>
                        <li> <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:white;text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px grey;background-color:silver;font-size:x-large"font-size:larger">Shree Brahma said:  </span>On hearing t,hese words of the mother of
                        the universe replied smilingly after thinking on Siva. </li>
                        <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:#ff4811;ffont-size:x-large"font-size:larger"> The Goddess Said  </span>
                        <li>Dear one, 0 Daksha Prajapati, listen to my weighty words. I tell you the truth. I am much delighted by your devotion. I shall bestow everything.</li>
                        <li>Subservient to your devotion, 0 Daska I, the great Goddess, shall be born of your wife as your daughter. There is no doubt in this.</li>
                        <li>0 sinless one, I shall perform a penance strenuously and shall become Siva's wife, after I have secured a boon from Him to that effect.</li>
                        <li>Otherwise there is no chance of the fulfilment of the object. The lord is free from all aberrations. He is the full incarnation of Sadasiva, worthy of being served
                        by Brahma and Vishnu </li>
                        <li>I am His slave for ever, His beloved in every birth (incarnation). Siva who manifests Himself in many forms is indeed my master.</li>
                        <li>It was by His favour that He manifested through the eyebrows of Braluna. I too shall incarnate by His favour and at His bidding.</li>
                        <li>0 dear one, go back to your residence. I have known my mission. Born as your daughter, ere long I shall be Siva's wife.</li>
                        <li>Having spoken these splendid words, She sought and obtained Siva's permission through mental communion.  While thinking on Siva's lotus-like feet, the Goddess spoke as
                        follows :-</li>
                        <li>But 0 Prajapati, you have to take a vow. It is a precondition. I shall tell you. It is true, never false, please understand.</li>
                        <li>If in future you were to be less respectful to me I will cast off my body. I shall withdraw myself to my soul or take to another form. It is true.</li>
                        <li>0 this boon has been granted to you. At · every creation I shall be born as your daughter and
                        become the beloved of Siva. </li>
                        <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:white;text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px grey;background-color:silver;font-size:x-large"font-size:larger">Shree Brahma said:  </span>
                        <li> After speaking thus to Daksa the chief Prajapati, the great Goddess immediately vanished even as Daksa was watching </li>
                        <li>When she· had vanished, he returned to his hermitage. He rejoiced because he knew that the great Goddess would become his daughter</li>
                           </ol> <a href=\'#top\'><strong>Back To Top</strong></a></p>`,
