                              subsections: [
                                { 
                                     subTitle: '',
                                     content: `
                                    <ol> <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:#FF000A;font-size:larger"> Narada said:  </span> 
                                    <li>On hearing the ethereal voice what did the unwise Daksa do ? What did the others do ? What happened thereafter ? Please narrate. 0 intelligent one,
                                    please tell me what those attendants of Siva who were  defeated by the power of Bhrgu's mantras did and where they went. </li>
                                    <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:white;text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px grey;background-color:silver;font-size:x-large">Shree Brahma said:  </span>
                                    <li>On hearing the voice of the Sky, the devas and others were stunned with surprise. They did not say anything. They stood perplexed and dazed. The remaining attendants of Siva who were defeated
                                    and routed by the power of Bhrgu's mantras fled and sought refuge in Siva.</li>
                                    <li>Bowing with great respect to Siva of immeasurable splendour they narrated everything that transpired there. </li>
                                    <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:brown;font-size:larger">Ganas said:  </span></em>
                                    <li>0 lord of Devas, save us who have sought refuge in you. Please listen with condescension to the detailed description of the events connected with Sati. </li>
                                    <li>0 Lord, great disrespect was shown to Sati by the haughty and wicked Daksa. The devas too did not show due respect to her. </li>
                                    <li>He did not allot your share but gave it to all the devas. The extremely haughty Daksa wickedly and loudly spoke harsh words. </li>
                                    <li>0 lord, not seeing your share in the sacrifice Sati became angry. After censuring her father many times she burnt her body (in the yogic fire). </li>
                                    <li> Ganas exceeding ten-thousand put an end to their lives out of shame by cutting off their limbs with weapons.  We, the rest, became infuriated. </li>
                                    <li>Assuming a terrifying attitude we suddently got ready to destroy the sacrifice. But we were repelled by Bhrgu by means of his (spiritual) power. He opposed us. </li>
                                    <li>0 lord; the sustainer of the world, we have now sought refuge in you. We are now grieved and fear-stricken. Please make us free from fear. </li>
                                    <li>0 great lord, Daksa and the other wicked persons have shown great disrespect because they are very haughty. </li>
                                    <li>0 bestower of honour we have told you all that  happened to us and to Sati. Please deal with those deluded  fools in the manner you deem fit. 
                                    </li>
                                    <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:white;text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px grey;background-color:silver;font-size:x-large">Shree Brahma said:  </span>
                                    <li>On hearing the words of his attendants, the lord remembered you, Narada, in order to know their activities.</li>
                                    <li>0 celestial sage, endowed with divine vision you reached the place and after bowing to Siva with devotion you waited there with palms joined in reverence. </li>
                                    <li>After· praising you, the lord asked you about Sati's news at the sacrifice of Daksa and the incidents there.</li>
                                    <li>0 dear, when you were thus asked by Siva, you identified with Siva and narrated to him in detail about what had happened in Daksa's sacrifice.</li>
                                    <li>0 sage, on hearing the words spoken by you, Siva became furious in a trice, Siva of great fury and valour.</li>
                                    <li>Then Rudra, the destroyer of the world, plucked out a cluster of his matted hair and struck the top of the  mountaip. with it.</li>
                                    <li>0 sage, the cluster of the matted hair of the lord split into two, on being struck on the mountain. A loud explosive sound was heard which was as terrific as the sound
                                    at the time of dissolution.</li>
                                    <li>0 celestial sage, from the first half of that cluster of matted hair, rose up the powerful Virabhadra, the terrific leader of the Ganas.</li>
                                    <li>He stood lofty with two thousand hands blazing like the consuming fire. He enveloped the world all round and towered over it ten inches more.</li>
                                    <li>From the furious breath of Siva, the great Rudra, hundred fevers and thirteen humours came out.</li>
                                    <li>From the other half of the cluster of matted hair
                                    Mahakali<noteref1_note1footer>(1) - (320)</note> was born. 0 dear one, she was very terrible and was surrounded by crores of goblins.</li>
                                    <li>The ruthless fevers had embodied forms. They were capable of terrifying the world. They were blazing with their :fiery splendour.</li>
                                    <li>hen the heroic Virabhadra, eloquent in speech, joined his palms in reverence and bowed to lord Siva. Virabhadra said thus .-</li>
                                    <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:darkblue;text-shadow: 3px 3px 2px white;background-color:skyblue;font-size:larger"> Virabhadra said:  </span>
                                    <li>0 Rudra of terrific appearance, with the moon, the sun and the fire for your eyes what am I to do ? 0 lord, command me quickly. </li>
                                    <li>0 Siva, are the oceans to be dried up in half a moment ? 0 Siva, are the mountains to be ground into powder in half a moment.</li>
                                    <li>0 Siva, shall I reduce the whole universe to ashes in a moment ? Shall I reduce the gods or the sages to ashes in a moment ?</li>
                                    <li>0 Siva, shall the destruction of the universe be carried out ? Or, 0 Siva, shall the harassment of all living beings be carried out ?</li>
                                    <li>0 lord Siva, thanks to your favour there is nothing  impossible for me. A person equal to me in valour has not been born, nor will he be born.</li>
                                    <li>0 lord, wherever you send me and on whatever  errand, I shall execute that job quickly and earn your favour.</li>
                                    <li>At your bidding, 0 Siva, even worthless persons  swim across the ocean of the world. 0 Siva, am I not therefore competent to cross the ocean of great adversity ?</li>
                                    <li>0 Siva, there is no doubt in this that even the blade of grass. despatched by you will achieve great tasks without difficulty in a moment.</li>
                                    <li>0 Siva, verily any task can be fulfilled by your mere sport. But it is your blessing and favour, that I shall be sent to do the job.</li>
                                    <li>It is by your blessing that I am qualified in this task. 0 Siva, without your blessing and favour none will have that power and efficiency.</li>
                                    <li>This is true. ·There is no doubt in this that without your command and permission no one shall move even a blade of grass.</li>
                                    <li>0 Siva, devas and others are subject to your control. I too am subject to the control exercised by you.  I am the controller of all living beings.</li>
                                    <li>0 Siva, I have knelt before you. Again and again I kneel before you. 0 Siva send me immediately for the fulfilment of your desire.</li>
                                    <li>0 Siva, my right limbs throb frequently. I am sure to be victorious today. 0 lord, so please send me.</li>
                                    <li>I feel a peculiar exhilaration and zeal. 0 Siva, my mind sticks to your lotus-like feet. </li>
                                    <li>At every step a senes of auspicious things and events have occurred. </li>
                                    <li>Surely he alone 'is victorious for ever, his alone is the welfare every day who, 0 Siva, is firmly devoted to you who are the resort of everything auspicious.</li>
                                    <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:white;text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px grey;background-color:silver;font-size:x-large">Shree Brahma said:  </span>
                                    <li> On hearing these words ofVirabhadra, the .consort of Sati became glad. He blessed him saying "O Virabhadra  be victorious" and said these words thereafter:-</li>
                                    <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:darkblue;text-shadow: 3px 3px 2px white;background-color:skyblue;font-size:xx-large"> Lord Shiva said:  </span>
                                    <li>0 dear Virabhadra, listen to my words attentively. You must carry them out quickly. It will then delight me.</li>
                                    <li>Daksa the wicked son of Brahma, has made arrangement to perform a sacrifice. He is particularly inimical to me. He is unwise and conceited now.</li>
                                    <li>0 best of Ganas, destroy the sacrifice with all the adjuncts and then return to my abode quickly.</li>
                                    <li>Even if there be devas, Gandharvas, or others, reduce them also to ashes quickly.</li>
                                    <li>Let there be Brahma, Visnu Indra or Yama. Fell them to the ground now itself with strenuous efforts.</li>
                                    <li>Transgressing the imprecations of Dadhici whoever stays in the sacrifice shall be burnt by you of course.</li>
                                    <li>If Visnu and others, out of erroneous notions were  to withstand, other will come for your help. They shall burnt by you after dragging them with mantras.</li>
                                    <li>Transgressing my injunctions many haughty persons are lingering there. They are also my enemies. So burn them with a series of blazing fire</li>
                                    <li>After reducing them to ashes, along with their wives, and all the paraphernalia at the sacrifice of  you shall return quickly.</li>
                                    <li>It is possrble that when you go there, devas and  others may praise you. Still you shall burn them in the flames. </li>
                                    <li>Burn the devas too who have committed offence, in the blazing fire, after meditating on me, your protector.</li>
                                    <li>After burning and all others along with
                                    their wives and kinsmen, without any effort, in a playful
                                    manner you shall drink waters.</li>
                                    <em><span style="font-weight:900;color:white;text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px grey;background-color:silver;font-size:x-large">Shree Brahma said:  </span>
                                    <li>After saying thus to Virabhadra the great hero, Siva the lord of all, the slayer of Kala, the protector of Vedic conventions, stopped, with his eyes still resembling copper
                                    (due to anger) </li>
                                   </ol> <a href=\'#top\'><strong>Back To Top</strong></a></p>`,
                                    notes: [`320. Mahakali is represented with a black skin, a hideous or terrible countenance, dripping with snakes, hung round with skulls and human
                                        heads, and in all respects resembling a fury rather than a Goddess. 
                                        `]
                                 }
                             ]
